SIMPLE: colophon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colophon
<hw>Col"o*phon</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*f⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>colophon</ets> finishing stroke, Gr. <grk>kolofw`n</grk>;
cf. L. <ets>culmen</ets> top, <ets>collis</ets> hill. Cf.
<er>Holm</er>.]</ety> <def>An inscription, monogram, or cipher,
containing the place and date of publication, printer's name, etc.,
formerly placed on the last page of a book.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>colophon</qex>, or final description, fell into disuse,
and . . . the title page had become the principal direct means of
identifying the book.</q> <rj><qau>De Morgan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The book was uninjured from title page to <qex>colophon</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colophonite</ent>⟦br⟧
